                <h1>What is a Function?</h1>
        <p>A function in C is a reusable block of code that performs a specific task. It allows you to break down your program into smaller, manageable parts, making your code more organized and easier to understand.</p>
        <p>Functions are like recipes; they take input (parameters), perform operations, and return output (if necessary).</p>
            </div>

