                <h1>Function Structure</h1>
        <p>A function in C typically consists of:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Function Declaration:</strong> Declares the function's name, return type, and parameters (if any).</li>
            <li><strong>Function Definition:</strong> Contains the actual code that defines what the function does.</li>
            <li><strong>Function Invocation (Calling):</strong> The process of using the function in your code.</li>
        </ul>
            </div>

        </div>

        <div class="slide">
