                <h1>Importance of Function Prototype</h1>
        <p>A function prototype declares the function's name, return type, and parameters without providing the function body. It informs the compiler about the function's existence before its actual definition, allowing you to use the function before defining it.</p>
        <pre><code>int add(int a, int b); // Function prototype</code></pre>
            </div>
